2774 Livermore Outlets DrSte 3170Livermore, CA 94551


        (925) 273-6156
    






We are fans of Columbia Sportswear Company.  This branch at the San Francisco Premium Outlet mall in Livermore, CA is no exception.

It is one of the larger stores that we have patronized.  More inventory choices makes for greater selection.  Store was well organized and clean.  Staff was helpful and answered our questions.  We scored some terrific deals at their Clearance sections!

Recommend checking out this Columbia store for your sportswear needs.







Great inventory.  I love their Omni tech clothing line. 

Great savings if you shop when they've got a holiday savings like President's weekend, Thanksgiving weekend, etc.







Great deals! I got a fleece jacket for $20, originally priced at $60! They have a large selection for both men and women.







Leah the supervisor in charge today was INCREDIBLY RUDE to me. She displayed a total lack of customer service concerning my return. I understand your "policy," but you DO NOT address customers in the cold and unprofessional way that she did to me. I was simply asking for STORE CREDIT for an item purchased 20 days ago with which I have A RECEIPT AND THE CREDIT CARD USED FOR THE PURCHASE. She was incredibly cold and told me t go ahead and call her corporate office to complain.

DO NOT BUY ANYTHING IN THIS STORE or AT ANY COLUMBIA STORE, OR THAT MATTER. REI had the best return policy and sells Columbia items. They don't treat their customers like thieves and deviants EVER.







The workers here are very friendly and helpful. I was looking for a winter jacket but since Im always cold it would be an everyday jacket. I been eyeing this jacket for 2 months but decided to wait since it was still summer, but with the approach of winter coming a long and the announcement of 30 new stores I have decided to hit this outlet up again. 

I still don't agree with the name of this outlet as I don't think it would draw more people in let alone tourists. But I am glad I went on a whim with my friend and made a day out of it. They had a good sale at this time 25% off additionally. The jacket I wanted was priced at $169.99 with an additional 25% off it came down to $130 before taxes but at checkout it rang for $90!!!!   The cashier told me it was on sale because it was last year's style. SCORE!

The customer service here is superb. I asked for 2 different sizes and they were happy to assist me. Everyone I encountered was very friendly and accommodating and because of this I will always return!







This Columbia Sportswear Outlet is located inside the Livermore Premium Outlets and although yes they may have some sales and all my family and I never end up purchasing anything from this store.

They have nice clothing and all specifically for outdoors, but it's just that prices here are too freaking high!!!! This is a pretty expensive store, so the quality is good but it's just too expensive!!

It's worth taking a look I suppose though...







I have gotten my favorite jacket here and at an awesome price! I love the selection. Definitely better deals during the week.







A disappointment where an outdoor store carries so little men's choices. I was happy until walking in and seeing the less than a quarter of the store with men's clothing. So about 5 different pants, 8 different shirts, 5 different vest, and 20 different jackets. 

The rest is women's, children'sand accessories.







Im headed to truckee for my first snowboarding in 2 days..I'm doing last minute snow gear shopping..we actually drove from Daly City to Livermore with my friend to shop here..the store is nice, lots of discounted clothing, jackets, winter gear etc..from 25% to 40% off..everything seems to be well stocked..right now im actively yelping while inside this store ..five stars goes out to Jacqueline!! Whose excellent customer service, politeness, honesty and her desire to assist customers really made my first Columbia gear buying experience a pleasant one!! Thank you for helping me get my first snow pants..with this positive experience, I'll be a repeat Columbia costumer..oh yes their gear are also comfy and will keep you warm and dry..







The products are worth checking out!
Compared to North Face, this is a cheaper alternative that you can afford.

Pros:
-Great, big selection of items
-Good amount of staff on the floor
-Clean and well lit

Cons:
-Staff should be properly trained to where all general items are
("Where can I find the snow pants?" 'Sorry, I don't know') That doesn't help...

Tips:
-Last time I came in they hired a bunch of new college level workers, FOBs at the job. It was hard to find a worker who knew where selected items were
-Weekends have the best sales (Nothing during weekdays)
-College student discount with ID card







I"m not sure if it was a hit-or-miss thing...but i came here for the 1st time and was able to find a few items. They were good prices, much better prices I got from the North face.  I was able to find 2 jackets and a top and some shoes. I will return to get a couple of more items next time. I also went to the other outlet location but was unable to find anything so i believe this location has a much better stock.







When making a return with a receipt, if the cashier ask to see your ID, just show them,  Do Not hand your ID to them. The cashier will scan your ID without telling you beforehand. I am not sure what they will do with your info, and they will say it is protocol which is not a good explanation.







Amazing service Anthony and Levi are very knowledgeable and made me feel very comfortable with the purchases I made! 5 stars I'll be coming back soon







Pretty good selection of ski jackets when I went. I found a great deal on the jacket and ski pants I purchased. I also found a couple of other sweaters I liked for my weekend in the snow that were marked down. I signed up for their rewards program online the night before, and they were nice enough to honor the 10% discount (only valid in-store). 

The staff was friendly and helpful. I liked this store and plan to come back next time I need some more gear.







Meh, they didn't have anything that spectacular here & the prices were barely discounted.. You can find a better selection & better prices online.







If you catch a sale the prices are good.  The service is excellent; despite it being a crowded, crazy weekend the staff were cheerful and helpful.  The salesperson went into the back to pull the size I needed, which was not on the floor, and I got a lovely new gray fleece for 25 dollars.  I love my other Columbia fleece and wear it almost year round, so I'll use the new fleece a lot too.  The selection isn't outstanding but it's good enough.  I do recommend trying clothes on there if you are going to buy online, to get an idea of sizing.  I wear a size small in almost everything, but in Columbia clothes I am more comfortable in a medium, especially to have room to wear things under the jacket or fleece.







The best place to shop for outerwear in the East Bay.

Columbia Sportswear has super awesome technology meant to withstand all sorts of weather.

The people who work here are knowledgeable and friendly.

The prices are spectacular. I got a pair of SOREL boots for really cheap. Their clearance shoe table is always stocked.

In my opinion, Columbia is waaay better than Northface and the garments last that much longer.

With a new location out in the Tri-Valley, hikers, runners, and skiers alike will definitely find something for themselves.







Do you need sporty clothes?  How about outdoors clothes?  Then you should go to the Columbia outlet.  They had a good selection of new things and helpful people. 

The clothes were laid out like any store, nicely on racks.  The selection seemed very similar to what I would find at REI or otherwise, regular in season, normal clothes with a variety of sizes, at a significant discount.

I was asked if I needed help a few times.  They ended up starting a room in the fitting area for me and even brought other sizes when the clothes I had didn't fit. Of course I think the ratio of staff to guests was close to 1:1 when I went so they should pay attention!







Came here during a 4th of July weekend sale and this place was crazy! Tons of good deals, but it was hard to find your size since there were sooo many people around. The store was clean, but with lots of people = messy store. The line to the dressing room was ridiculously long, but people moved in an orderly fashion.

Overall,  I found great hiking pants and a sweater here all for less than $80. Great quality and good deals during an event. I would recommend shopping here  if you are at the outlets. Friendly staff and good lighting.







Check in tip: Last minute snow boarding gear shopping for spontaneous Tahoe trip!

I have been here a few times, they have good selection for winter and sports wear and other swag! 

I was able to get my snow pants for $79, that's 50% off from its original price!







