What is this?







Columbia Sportswear Company is a leading innovator in the global apparel, footwear, accessories and equipment markets. We design, develop, market and distribute active outdoor and lifestyle products under the following brands:

Founded in 1938, Columbia brand apparel, footwear, accessories and equipment have earned a global reputation for innovation, quality and performance, keeping outdoor enthusiasts in more than 100 countries, warm, dry, cool and protected year-round.
Learn more at www.columbia.com.



SOREL combines a rich heritage of expert craftsmanship, durability and functionality with luxurious materials and styling to inspire a new generation of fashion-forward female consumers. SOREL is expanding its product offerings to include more year-round styles and product categories and is carried by premium footwear retailers throughout North America and Europe. Sorel was founded in Canada in 1962 and acquired by Columbia Sportswear in 2000.
Learn more at sorel.com, on Facebook at www.facebook.com/sorel, or @SorelFootwear on Twitter.


Mountain Hardwear is a leader in premium outdoor apparel and equipment and works with era-defining alpine athletes to develop innovative products and technologies. Mountain Hardwear, based in Richmond, California, was founded in 1993 and acquired by Columbia Sportswear in 2003. 
Learn more at www.mountainhardwear.com.


PrAna is a lifestyle apparel brand that draws its name from the ancient Sanskrit word for breath, life and vitality of the spirit. Based in Carlsbad, California, prAna creates mindfully-designed, purposeful and stylish clothing, prioritizing and pioneering sustainable practices in its operations and supply chain. PrAna was founded in 1993 and joined Columbia Sportswear’s family of brands in 2014.
Learn more at www.prana.com.

