            Stop following Gerry H.
        














        2/3/2014
    








            Listed in Businesses that have no business being in business.


Like several other notable, formerly proud, and once market leading companies (see Ray-Ban, Hoover Vacuum, et al.)Sorel has been purchased for it's brand cache and is systematically being transformed into a made in China (or Viet Nam) fashion focused, inferior product oriented, over priced corporate cash cow.  The heritage of quality and performance has been traded for return on investment.My expensive Sorels lasted exactly one hour in the sub-zero January temperatures that we have suffered recently in the midwest, before they completely disintegrated.  I returned them to the factory, based on the instructions provided by the customer service person at Sorel, and the warranty evaluator rejected my claim.  Technically, they were out of the warranty period, but when you drop a buck fifty on a pair of winter boots, you expect them to out perform your daughter's Hello Kitty boots.  That wasn't the case.  If you want an exceptional pair of extreme weather boots, grab a pair of US Army surplus "Mickey Mouse" boots manufactured by BATA.  They are  absolutey the warmest, most durable boots you'll ever own, and they're available all over the internet for bout $60.  Skip the junk that Columbia is cranking out in China and calling Sorel.




