        1/22/2017
    

I have a pair of Columbia boots that are a few years old. They are a winter boot that I wear only in the snowiest of conditions. I will never by a pair of Columbia boots again, in fact I'll never by a Columbia product again. The seams tore out of these boots rendering them useless in the winter. I wrote Columbia, but got no response. These are boots supposedly made for the toughest conditions, like Columbias moto, "tested tough", yeah right, Do Not Buy Columbia Boots, and if you expect customer service don't by Columbia products at all. It's sad because I use to be a fan of Columbia products. When I go to buy winter boots in the future I'll get Sorels.

















