        3/17/2016
    

I would put a big old Goose Egg (0) If I could!!!!  I want to be clear that I am reviewing the company customer service here, NOT the products.  The products have always been great, that's why what happened to me disheartens me even more.  :(If you order from online, you should be aware that if your package is lost (or in my case stolen) while in transit with UPS or FED Ex, Columbia "customer service" becomes your worst nightmare.  They should call it Columbia service instead of customer service, because they don't treat you like a valued customer when this happens to you.  I placed an order with a coat and mittens that they had on a great sale!  I tracked the package until it reached IL, and that is where it stopped, and my headache began!  I called Columbia (C) and told them that my package has not arrived by the ETA, and I was told that I need to wait at least 7 days past the ETA to see if it shows up.  Mind you, they have my $150.  They were willing and happy to take that, but I had no product!!  So, I patiently waited the 7 days, tracked the package again to the same distribution center in IL.  I called C back, and I was told that they would open up an investigation request.  They informed me that this could take 10-14 business days to complete.  So I asked, if I could have a refund or could they ship me a new package?  I was told that this is not their policy (by several other people as well in the company).  I was beside myself.  How could a company this huge treat me (a great frequent customer) as though it was my fault the package was lost.  they could have put a tracer on the package, and had (if found) it sent back to Columbia.  In the meantime, I should have gotten a new package and been thrilled w my purchase!  but NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO.  It didn't end there.  I wrote email after email call after call, and I kept getting told that the investigation with UPS was not complete (I have a friend with UPS access who said the invest was already closed and she sent me the notes).  The notes said that they found the mittens (outside of the box), and the jacket was never found.  The jacket was marked stolen, and the mittens were shipped back to C.  You know what I was told at this point???!!!!  I had to wait for the mittens to arrive back to C!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  I cant even tell you how livid I was!  Why do I have to wait for them to get the mittens back whne the invest. was closed and completed.  I finally got my money back a month after I ordered.  Thanks Columbia!  You lost a great customer.  Thanks but no thanks for the offer of 20% off an order.  You are all heart!!!!




