        1/25/2012
    

I disagree with the orange head review, Columbia is the bee's knees.I bought a Bugaboo parka in 2008 from some rando sporting goods site and we had several good years together. Sadly, the zipper died and I needed to send it in for repair just in time for a cold snap and of course I have a trip to Iceland coming up as well. Womp womp.So. Off to Oregon it went. Once I saw they received it I gave them a call to check on it and explain that I kinda needed it back and was answered by a lovely woman who listened to my plight and set about helping find a solution for me. She told me I was getting a replacement and we went through the options I had available to me, in less than half an hour a new coat was ordered and Columbia had made a huge fan out of me. A spankin new coat arrived at my office today and I love it. Columbia stands behind its products with great customer service, what more can you ask for?




